27/07/2004
VIENNA, Austria -- The leaders of eight Balkan nations are to meet in Salzburg on Tuesday (27 July) and Wednesday to discuss integration into NATO and the EU and the Kosovo issue. Austrian Chancellor Wolfgang Schuessel will welcome the prime ministers of Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Croatia, Macedonia, Romania and the constituent republics of Serbia-Montenegro. The meeting would provide an opportunity for "an informal exchange of views" on stability in Southeast Europe, according to the Austrian government. (AFP - 26/07/04)
